    "summary": "Shana is a Partner with PwC and serves the Firm in various capacities. She was elected in 2017 (and re-elected in 2021) as a member of the Global Board of PwC International Limited, overseeing the Firm\u2019s Network Leadership Team and its 295,000 professionals. She also chairs the Board of PwC Europe SE, a firm that oversees the PwC practices in Germany, The Netherlands, Austria, Belgium, Switzerland and Turkey.\n\nShana serves as an audit partner for major publicly listed multinational organizations. She was formally the Consumer Markets Leader for PwC Europe, overseeing client relationships and thought leadership in the Retail, FMCG and Transport/Logistics sectors. Shana began her career with PwC in 1994, making partner in 2011. She has worked with PwC throughout Canada, Cuba and the Netherlands. She has been the Vice Chair of the Board of Governors for the International School of Amsterdam (2013-2016), and is a member of the Young Professionals Committee of the American Chamber of Commerce in the Netherlands.\n\nShana graduated from the University of Waterloo with a Bachelor of Mathematics (Accounting) degree in 1997 and a Masters of Accounting in 1998. She holds designations as Chartered Professional Accountant (Ontario) and Certified Public Accountant (Illinois).\n\nPersonal Statement:\nI am passionate about the Retail and Consumer Industry. Connecting (and listening) to customers is key. Digitalization is bringing new business models to the table, disrupting the industry. Those companies that are creative, innovative and agile to change will be the future success stories.  \n\nI pride myself on client service delivered with a professional and common sense approach.  I try to introduce the right people, with the right expertise to work on solving the challenges companies are facing in today's dynamic environment.\n\n\n\n\n",
